.SH NAME
\f[B]elsereno\-security\f[R] \(em threat model, controls, and flags
.SH THREAT MODEL
ElSereno is operated by a single authorised operator on a workstation or
jump host.
The primary adversaries are:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Target\-controlled bytes\f[R] \(em responses from scanned hosts.
Mitigated by \f[I]render.SafeBytes\f[R] (bytes) and
\f[I]telemetry.SafeField\f[R] (strings at the log boundary).
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Credential exfiltration\f[R] \(em shell history, argv, \f[B]ps
e\f[R], \f[I]/proc//environ\f[R].
Never pass secrets on argv or via herestring.
Env vars leak via \f[I]/proc\f[R]; use a 0600 file for persistent
secrets or the encrypted vault (\f[I]elsereno creds store\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Audit tampering\f[R] \(em the audit log is a JCS hash chain with a
genesis marker, tombstoning purge, and an auditable rebase on compact.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]Supply\-chain\f[R] \(em reproducible builds (\f[B]\-trimpath\f[R],
\f[B]\-buildvcs=false\f[R]); releases signed with \f[B]cosign\f[R]; SLSA
L3 provenance; CycloneDX SBOM; \f[B]go\-licenses\f[R] enforced in CI.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
\f[B]Subprocess\f[R]
Only via \f[I]internal/exec.SafeCommand\f[R] with \f[I]CommandSpec{Name,
Flags, Positional}\f[R].
The \f[B]\(en\f[R] separator is always present.
.TP
\f[B]Vault\f[R]
AES\-GCM + Argon2id (\f[B]time=3, memory=64 MiB, threads=4\f[R]).
Master key is \f[B]unlock\-once\f[R], cached in
\f[I]memguard.LockedBuffer\f[R], zeroised on \f[B]vault lock\f[R] or
SIGINT / SIGTERM.
.TP
\f[B]CSRF\f[R]
Key derived from the vault master key via HKDF\-SHA256 with
\f[B]info=\(lqelsereno/csrf/v1\(rq\f[R].
\f[B]serve\f[R] requires the vault to be unlocked.
.TP
\f[B]Database TLS\f[R]
\f[B]database.tls_required\f[R] ∈ {\f[B]auto\f[R], \f[B]always\f[R],
\f[B]disable\f[R]}; \f[B]disable\f[R] is rejected at runtime on
non\-loopback hosts.
.TP
\f[B]Rate limiting\f[R]
Per\-IP 100/min (loopback exempt) AND per\-token 300/min; the more
restrictive limit wins.
.TP
\f[B]HTTP server\f[R]
Full timeouts (\f[B]5s\f[R]/\f[B]30s\f[R]/\f[B]30s\f[R]/\f[B]120s\f[R])
and 16 KiB header limit.
.TP
\f[B]Audit log\f[R]
JCS canonicalised over \f[B]id, occurred_at, actor, event_type, payload,
prev_hash\f[R].
Genesis \f[B]prev_hash = 0x00..00\f[R].
Tombstone purge preserves the chain; compact inserts a
\f[B]chain_rebase\f[R] marker and skips metadata entries.
.SH FLAGS AND ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]\-tags offensive\f[R] (build)
Enables writes, exploits, harvesting, and dialling.
Writes require triple confirmation.
Dialling additionally requires \f[B]\(endial\-allowed\f[R]; ≤ 3\-digit
numbers are hard\-blocked.
.TP
\f[B]ELSERENO_VAULT_PASSPHRASE\f[R] (env)
Emits a warning when a TTY is present; prefer \f[B]vault unlock\f[R] or
a 0600 file.
.SH EXIT CODES
Signals exit with \f[B]128 + signum\f[R]: SIGINT → \f[B]130\f[R],
SIGTERM → \f[B]143\f[R].
A second signal during drain exits immediately with the same code.
